Suddenly she stopped. Something was missing, was wrong. Glancing around on the mantle the mandolin was missing. Her face paled and she started to shake. <br>
Carefully she walked over to the mantle and closed her eyes, words of power, still weak in her usage of them flowed from her lips. Suddenly from the shadows she was able to see the one who took the Mandolin. Hear the words he uttered as he departed.<br>
